summary: A Mother's Love
title: A Mother's Love
body:
Robb tasted like pine, wild and enduring through even the roughest storms. His lips were what Janna imagined the feel of clouds would be like, soft and gentle with her, but she knew, like the rolling thunder, those lips could command the tens of thousands of men that followed them to slaughter any e

.

Janna was nearly asleep, the rhythmic sound of horse’s hooves padding on the ground below her, the motion of the horse almost like a mother rocking her child. She leaned back further against the warm,…
